##A month of volunteer drivers in Wuhan: 3 Loved Ones Die, still hanging on

Micro Signal biz-leaders

Function introduction, define Chinese commercial power

By Liu Qian
Source: biz-leaders

###By Liu Qian
Source: biz-leaders

By Liu Qian

Source: biz-leaders

Wuhan "closed city" , traffic shutdown, the city's urgent call for 6000 taxis. Wang Wenting, a Wuhan resident, signed up as a volunteer driver to pick up and drop off medical staff and community residents free of charge.

"Be a man with a clear conscience. " Her father, an old communist, supported her.

But the pillar of the same father fell, grandma, uncle died one after another. She lost three people in a month. She can't get the ashes, she can't have a funeral, she can't do anything, she's just secretly sad.

For Wuhan, like thousands of volunteers, she did her best. She looked forward to giving her mother a big hug when the epidemic was over, giving her children long-term companionship, making up for her father's regrets and allowing time to heal the wounds.

Here's Wang wenting's dictation:

Three loved ones have passed away

At 13:26 on February 24,2020, my father left me for good.

I skyped with my dad every day for 20 days while he was in the hospital. Then he got worse and started breathing, and I made him listen to me, just nod or shake his head, and we kept talking.

On the 22nd, Dad got sicker. In the evening, Dad sent a text, he said: "Tingting, if tonight dad can not hold, please do not blame me, dad tried. " I was really helpless, told him, "you must hold on, I can not do without you. "

He made it through. The next morning, like a child taking credit, he told me that he was eating breakfast, an egg, a steamed bread, a bowl of soup all finished. I was so happy to be rehabilitation that night, I thought it must have been physical strength to do it, and I called the doctor to see if dad was getting better, and the doctor said no, just to get his lungs working.

Every Day Dad would say, "I made it through today. ". I would praise him, "Dad, you are great, you are my hero, " so tease him, he would laugh. That day in the video, he and I made a gesture to refuel, I also act like a spoiled child to let my father to buy me a cell phone, he immediately transferred 10,000 dollars to me. I just want to give him a thought, must let him personally take me to buy, Dad listened to laugh, I remember that was the last time he smiled at me.

On the morning of the 24th, I asked my father, did you sleep well yesterday, he nodded, I asked again, how do you feel now, he shook his head. I saw my dad was in a lot of pain, and I wanted him to rest, so I hung up the video, but I didn't realize that when the video hung up, it was for life.

Maybe I thought too good, suddenly said rescue, I did not prepare for the thought. The doctor told me that my father's condition was very bad, Oxygenation only, I begged the doctor must save him. The doctor said, I know you're a volunteer, and we're going to do everything we can to save your dad. A little after one in the afternoon, the doctor called me and said, "sorry, we did our best. "

My father was born on September 15,1952 and died on February 24,2020, at the age of 67.

My uncle was the first one in the family to get sick. At the end of January, he caught a cold and had to run to the hospital for an examination. After waiting in line for four or five hours, he went home again. When he got back, he had a fever, and the C.T. showed that he was infected, which is really not true. Five days later, on February 1st, he died.

All of a sudden, there's no one there.

After uncle was infected, dad took over to take care of grandma. He knew it was dangerous, but he went anyway, because my dad was a good son. Mom didn't want him to go, but dad said he hadn't been around since he was a kid, and now he wanted to be filial, and if his mom died, even if he lived, he would have regrets for the rest of his life.

Grandma ninety-year-old, lying in bed can not move, has been called uncomfortable, dad heard the noise on the rise, almost five days five nights without sleep, has been drinking white rice porridge with grandma. The precautions are to wear a mask 24 hours a day, two or three layers, but in this case, how do you not get infected.

The Day Dad was quarantined, grandma died at home. Until death, we do not know whether grandma was infected, the final cause of death is "respiratory failure. ". From uncle to grandma to dad, it's called making a mistake, every step.

Many people ask me, your father after taking care of grandma do not regret, I said he will not regret, I believe he did not regret to go to heaven. I supported his decision just as he supported mine.

I'm a volunteer driver

On December twenty-eight, the day before the "closure" of the city, my company, trip T3, called on us to join the ranks of volunteers. I signed up at that time.

My father, an old communist, told me to be a man with a clear conscience. He set a good example for me, and I want to set a good example for my children, by telling them that what mom is doing now, is contributing to society, and that you should be contributing to society when you grow up.

I didn't tell my family until I signed up. My husband was silent. My mom says it's too dangerous. Think about it. You have two kids. My father was silent for a moment and said, you've already signed up. There's no way you can quit. If you want to do it, if you think you can do it, you do it. I'll cover for you.

On the second day of the Lunar New Year, I was assigned to Donghu New Technology Development Zone, fifty kilometers from home. Every day at 9:30 work, 5:30 work, mainly responsible for transport needs of residents, as well as help residents buy food, buy medicine.

Wang wenting right work photo

There was a very long line of people, one meter apart, waiting two or three hours at a time. I usually collect the needs of the residents, and then inform the owner of the pharmacy to let him ready in advance, while the less time to go to get away, but the cold medicine can not be bought. My job doesn't allow me to go to crowded places. I'm responsible for myself and everyone else.

The same is true of shopping. I Buy Food for my family for several days at a time. When I deliver food and medicine, my husband and I never see each other, I drive downstairs, put things in one place, call my husband, sit in the car far away to see him take, tell him must first disinfection and then take home.

Our family has been very strong sense of prevention, in mid-january, in and out of the mask, I will be after work every day in the home and the corridor with disinfectant spray again. Masks are very hard to buy, I did not buy from the pharmacy, do volunteers, the company gave us a mask, protective clothing, goggles. At first some of the elderly did not even wear masks, the community workers persuaded them to wear them, see no mask, we will give their own to them.

In early February, I was transferred to serve the medical team from Suzhou and needed to be on call 24 hours a day. I checked into the hotel where the medical team was staying. Before getting into the car, both sides first take body temperature, all the way open the window ventilation, after getting out of the car, I will spend 20 to 30 minutes to the car disinfection, back to the room after their body disinfection. It can take up to 20 minutes to get there and back, and it can take up to an hour to clean and sanitize.

In the car, I will not take the initiative to accost, they have been very hard, sometimes want to be quiet, do not use your language to "harass" them, is my own request. To Ask about my dad's illness, I feel like I've gone too far, and they're always so concerned, giving me advice and confidence.

The first day of the medical team was the same day my dad went from quarantine to the hospital. I drove the medical team more than a dozen times that day, working until 4 a.m. , when I saw that they were short of supplies and contacted volunteers to donate 135 washbasins, 160 boxes of mineral water, disinfectant and protective clothing for the hotel, dad Wasn't much help.

I believe good things happen to good people, and there was a little bit of superstition, hoping that God would see what I was doing and look out for my dad.

When I got the call that my father had died, I was at the hotel helping to move supplies, and I burst into tears. But I do not regret this choice, even if I am at home, it is not possible to go to the hospital to take care of Dad, and stay on the front line let me get a lot of information and advice, can share to dad. He knows we all did our best, and I'm sure dad would be proud of me.

After Dad died, the company gave me three days off, and I needed to adjust to not bringing negative emotions to work. Now, my idea is very simple, as long as I need, I will continue to insist. I'm doing it with my father's dying wish, to do it better, to show my father that his daughter is no worse than he is.

Carry on with Dad's dying wish

My father-in-law is actually my father-in-law. My mom left me when I was a kid, and my dad died when I was 23. At 25, I married my husband, and for 10 years, my parents-in-law treated me as their own daughter. In my heart, they were my father and mother.

Dad loved me the most. I was tired as a lyft driver, and when I got home, my father brought food and drink directly to my hand; in the cold winter, he took a hair dryer to help me heat up the quilt; he was usually very frugal, reluctant to eat and also reluctant to wear, but as long as I came home to eat, it was very rich, he can't even buy his own clothes for more than $100, and he doesn't hesitate to wire me $10,000 for a cell phone.

He couldn't make good on his promise to take me to buy a mobile phone, which made me regret it forever. I'm sorry I couldn't give him a ride.

Now is such a helpless, know family sick, can not see, know family died, can not send, know family cremated, can not get ashes, also can not set up funeral hall, can not do anything, can only hide at home, secretly sad.

But what can you do? Life goes on. I video-chat with my father the other day, you can rest assured that I will take care of the home, I believe that my father is leaving with this sentence, he will be relieved, I will do.

I haven't seen my kids in over a month, and they skype me every night, to make sure I'm okay, and they say, mom, you have to protect yourself, and when you're done, come back with us. They never say, no, they just say, my mom is a big hero, and I'm going to be just like my mom.

I don't think I'm a hero for this kind of behavior. This is what people in Wuhan should do. We don't do it for others, we do it for ourselves. We also do some very ordinary things. I hope Wuhan will get better soon.

When this is over, the first thing I'm GonNa do is go home and hug my mom. I also want to take my mother to see where my father went to the countryside many years ago. My father used to say that he wanted to go back to see it, but he never did.

The dead are gone, the living must continue, although the psychological wound may take a long time to repair, but I think it will be good, optimistic face, in order to let oneself go better, also can let the deceased rest in peace.

The epidemic brutally deprived many people of their lives, but it also taught us the value of life, told us that there really is warmth in the world. After the outbreak, our Wuhan will be like a real family more unity, at least in my mind is so.

* Photo provided for interviewees
